<subSubSection id="5A9465406E5B3F194044FB49FE4D9244" pageId="15" pageNumber="104" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="123136CB6E5B3F194044FB49FE4D9244" blockId="15.[270,1103,1199,1620]" pageId="15" pageNumber="104">
<emphasis id="20FAEAD96E5B3F194044FB49FE019394" bold="true" box="[296,410,1199,1220]" pageId="15" pageNumber="104">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Elytra bright coppery green. Mentum with median tooth short and markedly bifid, length 
<emphasis id="20FAEAD96E5B3F19435DFB2FFDD8938F" bold="true" box="[561,579,1225,1247]" pageId="15" pageNumber="104">⅓</emphasis>
that of lateral lobe. Tarsomere 5 of posterior leg long and inserted into markedly emarginate tarsomere 4. Elytron with sutural apex acute (5b, c).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
